<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-circles-chords-and-tangents" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Circles, Chords and Tangents</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
        In this chapter, we will explore the properties of circles, chords, and tangents. We will learn how to construct tangents to circles, understand the alternate segment theorem, and investigate the relationships between intersecting chords, secants, and tangents. Additionally, we will examine how to draw tangents between two circles, as well as different circles that can be constructed from a given triangle. Finally, we will look at real-life applications of these concepts.
    </p>
    <p>
        Many sections focus on geometric constructions, where you use a compass and straightedge to create geometric figures. It is important that you practice these constructions to develop your understanding of the properties of circles and their related elements.
    </p>
  </introduction>

